      </p>

     </div>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA09d345n1-ptr" id="PJA09d345n1">1</a>
      
   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> enclosed the forged letter from Clinton to Lord George Germain in his letter to Edmund Jenings of 30 May (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>, enclosure not found). For a brief publication history of the Clinton letter, see <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s letter of 21 May to C. W. F. Dumas, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-09-02-0209&amp;expandNote=PJA09d228n1#PJA09d228n1" class="document">note 1</a> (above).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA09d345n2-ptr" id="PJA09d345n2">2</a>
      
   <p>Therefore it [<ins title="editorial addition or explanation" class="ed">Congress</ins>] has determined upon on such letters as this, which cannot deceive the public for a moment, to better advance its war effort.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA09d345n3-ptr" id="PJA09d345n3">3</a>
      
   <p>Jean Luzac.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA09d345n4-ptr" id="PJA09d345n4">4</a>
      
   <p>A false report.</p>

